,Recommended,302270,11537989,"Posted: 3 August, 2014",all,GamingChocobro,"Now. As a player of the original Dungeon Defenders, I looked forward to this. Now, unlike everyone else.. ranting and raving about how Crap this is. Let me start off with the good stuff.1: You don't have to pay to unlock all the characters. They are all there ready for you.2: The UI for your Character Sheet is much better. It allows you to easily swap over gear3: The bonus of your armour ACTUALLY changes when you put it on. For EG: I picked up a crown and I saw the crown on my charaters head.4: The abillity to create a character and name it without having to go out of the game and back to the menu to name it, colour it, and all that.5: The open tavern. Alot don't like the idea as Whining, Rude people, Noobs and such. The open tavern is a place where people can meet up, stuff like that instead of having a game on a menu to pick from. and not knowing who you might be playing with. At least with the open tavern, you can get a rough idea.6: The abillities. Nothing makes Dungeon Defenders like the placement of towers and useage of abillities. That is still all there, but with a little more. There are now ingame items which can be used to assist gameplay. Of course these can be bought from the tavernkeeper, or you can find them randomly drop from Goblins, Orcs, Dark Elves and the such or from chests.7: The Character Model. The Character sheet now has a model of your character. It allows for 360* rotation to view all angles of your character.8: Cross-Platform. Got a friend who is waiting for a new PC? Well why not buy them a copy of Dungeon Defenders Eternity on a different platform and let them play with you.9: Same classic music... it even sounds clearer10: The map selection is easier to traverse11: The portraits of the parents look better12: When dying, you have 6 colour slots instead of 3 making for more customization13: (Just Played Multiplayer) The drops are individual and so are the chests. no longer shared manaNow that I belive I have done all the Pros, its time for the cons.1: Lack of instant customization. Sure you can pick a skin to use on a hero, but to customize it more, you need to buy Dye from the tavern keep. Oh If you make a mistake, buy a bucket of white wash and start again with buying more dye.2: Limited Skins. Heroes have custom skins, but they are limited.3: One Server. From what I can tell, there is one server.4: The Cash Shop. Yep, the annoying Cash shop to get more stuff. Usually associated with Pay 2 Win games. Though in Dungeon Defenders Eternity, it is thankfully only for cosmetics.5: While an open tavern is good, It also does have its cons. With an open tavern, The abillity to move around is hard. The lack of space to find friends, or even preview your character are hindered.6: Online. Now, I know you might rage at this, saying online is a con? well, It is and it isnt. The con of the online is that if your not connected to the internet, you can't play.7: Currency. You no longer use Mana crystals. You use gold coins to buy stuff which you find randomly in chests and from enemy drops and buy sellling old gear. (Not to sure about after completing a wave or a map as my game wasn't completely downloaded when I stated to play)8: Wait time. You join a game wether its private or public and you have to wait.9: It doesn't use Steam UI for invites10: You can't customise your Crystal11: The Defence Units are shared among all players, including those playing summonerThere are more pros and cons, but as of this time of what I have played, This is all I can give. I am bound to do another Review after more playtime.Now, Some people might like the original Dungeon Defenders and hate this, or vice versa or like both. It doesn't matter as everyone is different. So I am not going to say YES buy this or NO don't buy this. I will let you decide if you want to buy it or not. I wouldn't based your decision on the reviews, but on videos on gameplay, demos or trying it at a friends place. But as a gamer and lover of Dungeon Defenders (note Dungeon Defenders was one of the first games I bought on steam when it first came out many years ago near christmas) I would recommend this if you want to just have fun without the worry of paying for more characters, maps, skins etc."
