ade the removal even more painful. They were drops after completing a level, and apparently you hatch pets in this game by putting them in one of your 4 amulet/consumable slots and getting exp. That was exciting to me, and I couldn't wait to see what I got.Also, to their credit and to defend the second log-in, they seem to have included TwitchTV streaming. Or, at least, I saw an option that had a sign-in for it and a ""start stream"" button. That's cool, now there might be a good number of DD streamers to help bolster the community.Overall, as the game is, it needs some work. Maybe buff the servers, or let there be an offline mode, even if it's completely separate from the online in terms of characters and loot and stuff. I'd probably recommend it if I could play it steadily, and since I can play larger games without connection issues, I don't think the problem is entirely on my end. I am prepared to edit my review, though, with future updates and any improvements they make, because this game has potential, and there are a lot of things I'd love to see from this game in DD2."
