76561198052071699,Not Recommended,302270,11400057,"Posted: 24 July, 2014",all,Ron,I bought the game yesterday and when i try to create a account it keeps on loading for 1 hour + but i cant say if this will get fixed after a couple of updates
,Recommended,302270,11502087,"Posted: 31 July, 2014",all,LordJJ,"Game Review:Pros:GameplayNew system allows for a more rebalanced look at the classic dungeon defenders and grants old players that new player experience. While some feel that this is not true, I feel after playing DD1 for hours on end that this is in fact true. Keep in mind that the game does not allow you to transfer over a character from DD1, so you will have to start over at level 0. Each game you play presents the same thing you saw in DD1, chests, monsters, etc. However the chests are now for you only. What does this mean? Every player sees a chest and, lets just say that if another player tries to take it then they would just opened a chest that was for them specifically, you still have yours! Pretty cool... this means more mana than normal to start with, if you have enough players.CoinsThe game drops coins and mana now. Mana is used for upgrading towers and using special abilities like amulets, pets, and hero skills. Coins are used for upgrading armor and weapon pieces. This does provide a nice divide between the fighting environment and the tavern environment.MicrotransactionsWait what? Why did I list this as a pro? Okay, so here's the deal. Trendy decided to setup any real money transactions that will allow people to buy emotes... and that's it. Good job on that one, I'm cool with this. If you need a little extra cash for emotes, I'll do that.AmuletsNew items have been added to help boost the gameplay. The amulets can do multiple types of abilities depending on which one of 4 you can bring into battle. Some of the abilities that you can choose are repair towers, weaken enemies, heal players, boost weapon damage, and so on.BlueprintsBlueprints drop randomly throughout maps you play. You can use ingredients found in chests to then craft the item on the blueprint at the craftmaster found in the tavern. Some people say that this provides an overall better stats item, however, I did not notice this. But I will say you can save the blueprint and make multiple weapons or armor if you wish, which is cool if you want to have multiple pieces of the same armor because it has awesome tower stats!InventoryThe new inventory system is much easier to useonceyou get through the challenges of learning how to manipulate the commands. For example ""M"" unlocks all items that are displayed, ""A"" sells all items that are displayed. I'm being specific in saying ""that are displayed"" because if they aren't displayed with your filter settings on, then you won't sell them on accident... huge bonus :) They also added folders just like the old game, however you have a bit more freedom with how many you can add. Oh yeah... did I mention 0/1000 slots? That's much better.DyesDyes are cool if you are into asthetics, however, I am not. But none-the-less this is an awesome feature for people who like to get off on detailed coloring of their armor pieces. The amount of detail that was added so you can completely customize the color scheme is, to me, a bit more than I care to do, especially since I'm swapping gear so often. Until the recent patch v3.2 you were unable to sell dye and it would stack in your inventory. Now it's been fixed.PetsPets are different in this game than the original DD1. In this game you find eggs and you hatch them by putting them in your amulet slots and let them get exp while you fight. Once it notifies you that the egg is ready to hatch then you go into a forge and inspect the egg. There will be an option to hatch the egg and it will produce for you a random pet. Each pet has it's own passive ability as well as an activated ability, which is hotkeyed to ""X"". This system allows you to experiment and determine which pet you want for yourself rather than run a map over and over for, I dunno, something like a kobold?ColorsWhile a lot of people complain about the color of the texture and say ""it's blurry"" etc, I want to let everyone know that the game does say ""Please allow for images to stream because they may be blurry in the beginning"", which was true. Once I allowed for the game to play for a while, the color system worked pretty well. There is a difference and after going back to DD1 to help a friend, I prefer the new DDE colors.Cons:Trendy Overlay MenuThe game no longer seems to be running through steam systems. When I attempt to go visit ""who I've partied with recently"" it no longer records them. In addition, the overlay menu that trendy uses is extremely difficult and in what appears to be a beta type version. Nothing is easy or smooth. To access the menu first press F11, completely out of the way and not as easy as Shift-Tab for Steam Overlay menu.Party SystemIf you want to party with your friends get ready for a challenge. If they are in the same tavern as you, awesome you are in luck! Press Esc and look for their name and ""add to party"", cool right? Okay what if they aren't one of the 16 players in the tavern? Sh!t.... ok go to Overlay menu F11, go to the second tab from the top, click right twice until you get to friends, click the dropdown on your friends name, click add to party and wait... did he add? Oh he's gotta accept.... ok he finally accepted. F11 to get back outta overlay menu. They could make it much more user friendly if they tried.Survival MapsSurvival maps used to be in waves, 1 to 35 for tavern defense in DD1. NO LONGER IS THIS TRUE, this is pretty cool in my book. This does present a problem because now you are confined to 1 character through the entire survival, not cool;  sometimes we want to level our alts. In addition to this issue there is also an issue with mana in the beginning. Each player has their own chest as mentioned before, which would limit you as a single player trying to build for an entire survival because you cannot switch and build the build completely as you would in DD1. For example Endless Spires Survival, if I run it as a single player I get 375 total from all the chests, if I have 3 other players I would get 1500 mana for my build because players can pool mana like in DD1. So at the moment survival sucks because we HAVE to bring in other players in order to build the build we want.KickingNone. They don't have it in the game. If you wanna go in and afk 24/7 to get up to level 60, go for it. The only thing they have to prevent afking is a very long timer that attempts to sense if you are afk after something like 25 minutes of ""not moving"" which doesn't include being dead. So if someone is afk and keeps dying, well they get to be in the game the entire time.Stage Selection & LFGThe stage selection screen is quite nice, however it's just my personal opinion that the screen is larger than need be and not as concise in the information presented. The biggest drawback looking for a game to play with random people is that you cannot see all of the maps that are in play. If you haven't completed the stage, it won't show for you if others have space. This really limits the number of people who join your game, especially if you are doing end game content and need the help of others.Scanning your lootThere is an issue that causes the game to not hold the comparison window up of an equipped item and an item you are mousing over. This blip of disappearance is on-set by people joining the tavern, and taverns are public so this happens very often.Should I buy it?The game has it's pro's and con's as you can see above. After being a fan of DD1 and coming to DDE I was originally seething with anger because of what I saw, however, now I can say that I really enjoy DDE more than DD1. You just gotta get in the game and play it a bit. It's worth it in the end and I support it, even with all it's terrors."
