76561198019366608,Recommended,302270,11454236,"Posted: 28 July, 2014",all,Gray_Paladin,"For those who don't know, Dungeon Defenders is technically a tower-defense game, where every map is essentially a PvE arena where you are protecting your central crystal. But, it has some fun RPG elements with the characters you choose.There was a lot of negative flack about this editiion when it was first released. I think the negative reactions where kneejerk and misguided. The company has worked to get their servers more responsive. That has been successful. The game has also had some very needed balances corrected from the original and I can enjoy the weaker classes much more than before. There have also been a huge number of elements added to the game (e.g., crafting, dyes, outfits, etc), and more sophisticated play together UI. The negative criticism also was directed at a lack of single player, but really, you can host a private session with yourself or with any friends you want to bring along any time you want. Really, it's an excellent and incredibly addicting game. If it seems hard at first try a squire first, apprentice second. Those two characters are far and away the most powerful. But, the ranger, and most of the other classes have become far more playable. Summoner is a blast but requires some sophisticated play.In any case, I recommend this game unreservedly, giving it about an 85% -- and I think it will continue to improve as the devs polish it further. Hang in and enjoy. It is a blast!"
