 they can.  However, in this case, they have to know by now that there is a major problem with the Linux client to this game.  Yet they still allow the game to be listed as ""Available on Linux"".  That makes them partially negligent in allowing this fraud to continue.Since I can't get my money back for this game, I'll give any reader patient enough to read to the end of my rant this advice:  Don't give Trendy a dime of your money for this POS until they get their act together and actually deliver what they promised!************** UPDATE 10/10/2014 *****************It looks like they've made some updates to the Linux client.  You have 4 options to launch now (not sure what they all mean).  The options are ""Play Dungeon Defenders Eternity"", ""Link Steam Libraries"", ""Unlink Steam Libraries"", ""Play Offline"".  For me they all do the same thing.  The application tries to launch and exits.  I get a flash of a window, but it's disappears so quickly I can't see anything to give me a useful hint as to what's going on.Trendy (or whomever is developing this now), you guys suck!!!"
