,Recommended,302270,11380728,"Posted: 23 July, 2014",all,Modkiq,"Don't care about the bad reviews that people with literally 0.2 hour playtime. I will provide you with a proper review for the game.I have no idea why this game is getting so many negative reviews. In this review I want to go over some of the things that they changed about the game.Before I start, this game is basicly Dungeon Defenders 1, with new content, and a lot of fixes.New ContentCash shopThe cash shop is getting a lot of hate by a lot of the reviewers. They are saying that it makes the game developers look greedy, and that they only care about money. This is false. The only thing you can buy in the cash shop, is taunts. You can buy taunts for $1 each, and there is a total of 34 taunts you can buy. It does not give you any benefits in the game, but it does make you very cool looking.The pause menuThey have made a new pause menu for the game, which does not only look amazing, but it is amazing as well. You can now change your options in game, without having to close, and re open the game. You can once again inspect players (look at their gear and stats), you can add randoms to your party without having to add them on steam, and you can report players for different reasons, like cheating, offensive username, language and profile picture.The tavernThey are using the same tavern as in the last game, but you are now sharing  the tavern with other players. This makes it possible for you to just sit in the tavern, and chat, make new friends, trade with randoms etc. It makes a community out of the game.Story mode, challenges, and just maps in general.They are using basicly all (and some new ones) maps form DD1, but they have made it so you have to complete them in order to be able to play them. This makes it so you can no longer but the game, and instantly lvl up to the max lvl. You have to work for your lvl, and you have to work for your gear. This makes it more funt o play with friends.Pets, armor, weapons.You can now see parts of the armor you are wearing, which is really cool. All the armor pieces does not look the same, like it does in the original game, and you no longer get armor with just +1 stats if you play on easy mode. This makes it way more balanced.For the pets, I think they have made a huge improvement. They have made it so all lvl 1 pets comes from eggs that you need to carry around (basicly just have it in your inventory) until they hatch, and you get a new pet. All pets have special abilities that you can use (with cooldowns), plus they will fight for you, like they did in the original game.For the weapons, I have ot noticed anything different yet, apart from the new textures.Coins!You no longer have to be greedy when you are upgrading your friend's towers with your mana, because you no longer use mana as money. They have made it so you get coins instead. This makes a lot more sense to me, as I think of magic, and summoning when I think of mana. I don't think about buying armor with it. You get coins about the same way you get mana. You get them form killing mobs, selling your loot, and completing maps.Small changesI have found a few small changes in the game too, that I think are really cool.When you are near another player, you can see their health and mana bar over their heads. Now you don't have ti pause the game to see if anybody has any mana left!There is a mini-map in the corner of the screen, so you don't have to enable the full-scree map to see where the remaining mana-chests are. You can just look at the mini map! You can of course use the large map too, if you perfer that.When you are building a tower, or repairing one, there is no longer a giant progress bar showing in the middle of the screen. They made a small, but nice looking bar down in the left corner instead.Keybinds for your forge. Now you have keybinds you can use in your forge, instead of having to click first the item, then the unlock button, you can simply click L while hovering your mouse over the item you wish to lock/unlock to do so. There are more keybinds like this.Things I don't like about the gameIt is a bit confusing the first 20 minutesYou kind of have to play DD1 to understand what's going on in this game. I guess you could always google a ""Dungeon Defenders Eternity tutorial"".The first time you load something, the textures are blurry as they render for the first time.They change a lot of things in the game without warnings. Suddenly they figure they want to remove single player, but after a while they add it again..-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------Overall, this is a very good game, and if you liked the old game, this is a must. I have 500 hours on the old dungeon defenders game, and I wouldn't be suprised if I got up to another 100 hours on this game.I don't know why this game got so many bad reviews (mostly by people that only played it for under 1 hour). I believe it is because it is so different from the first game. It takes some time to get used to the new things. People are getting mad when they see that there is a cash shop, but I don't think they should worry about it, as the cash shop only sells taunts. You can buy everything else for in-game coins! I really have no idea why they are calling this a phone-app though. It is just like DD1 in my opinion.Notice that the game is not a finished project. They game came out yesterday, and they are still working on things like bugs (haven't found any serious bugs yet), new content etc. You have a lot of things to look forward to if you buy this. It also has some sneak peaks on dungeon defenders 2, as they use some of the DD2 things in this game. And yes, they added private games, so you can play alone if you perfer that."
