 weapons or armour.buffs, agian this might be a personal thing but the fact that you can buy bombs etc makes it feel like the tower strategy has been made slightly easier.For thos who have never bought Dungeon defenders have to pay 20 while I should be 15 euro out of sale(I'm from Ireland so I only have the Irish price.)If you want to play a private game they make you wait through a 33 second timer.They made the gui aimed towards phones making it akward to use. once you learn the shortcut keys it is slightly easier to useThe idk:The fact that people can't host games is both a good and bad thing as It helps players find other players who want to play the same map but it also makes it very hard to setup a party of players who can work together properly e.g my first public game was throne room but  when I join my party was me and 3 barbarians luckily I could carry the team with my towers but if I had never joined that team was doomed from the start.There is microtransactions but they are emotes and in all my time playing Dungeon Defenders I don't think I ever used an emote so I can't say they're a good or bad thing.Conclusion:This game is in a grey zone as you can't call it a cash grab from dungeon defender fans as It's 6 euro right nowbut you also can't call it a new game as even though it has new things It's still the same game at its core.If your a fan of dungeon defenders you'll probably buy it anyway but if your a new comer think it through before you buy it as I think the 20 euro price tag is too high for a game that was released 3 years ago."
