,Recommended,302270,11378895,"Posted: 23 July, 2014",all,Admiral Beslan,"I was skeptical of this at first, with 600 hours in DD1, hating the RNG/end-game MASSIVE grind. but so far I'm super pleased with this.Pros:- All DLC is included (Although holiday dlc maps seem to not be in it), which means all that we no longer get the classic ""Oh damn, I haven't bought that map/character""- New equipment slots like a shield slot for everyone, two weapon slots allowing a backup elemented weapon (Like Series EV/Jester in Vanilla)4 new maps (And probably more coming)- So far the item RNG seems to be better (Can't tell because I haven't reached end-game yet)- Equipment actually shows on your character (I think you can turn this option off)- Mana is no longer the out of combat currency, enemies (and chests, and sold loot) now gives Gold Coins!- New slots for Consumables and Amulets that give you up to 4 new skills to use in battle, ranging from a simple health potion(Consumed on use!) to an amulet that lets you summon a thunder storm (With a cooldown of 60s)- Each pet now comes with it's own activated ability. i.e. Engineer lets you do a blast repair in an area, or the Heavy lets you buff you and surrounding allies' Hero damage for a period of time!- Summoner's Minions now use Defense Unit(DU) instead of having their own Unit pool. I think this is a plus because I felt we were being forced to use Minions as they effectively doubled (Or even triple since you don't need to use up half their points as walls) your defense strength / amount of placeable towers for damage.- All loot is instanced! No more loot ninjas! All Chests are instanced to you (and whatever come sout of them), I think dropped mana from enemies is NOT instanced though! So be fair for that, but all other loot, go nuts!- New Dash feature that lets you do some quick jumps ala UT/Quake style! (Although you have a stamina bar and right now you can only do it via the ctrl key, so no double tapping a direction for now)Cons:- It costs extra (But overall it's cheaper for new players, and 70% off for owners of DD1 now, which I feel is fair as the dev's have obviously put in a bunch of effort.- Always online (I think this is ALSO a plus, stops hackers, allows you to play while the big/highrez textures stream in (First time only, so expect some blurry textures at first but trust me they do get better)- In-App Purchases (But these are purely costmetic, right now they're just $1 emotes)- Public Tavern (Which is actually really good for some people but for me it causes big lag)- Slow internet means you will get lag, no matter your settings in game, but I think it's bareable. (Like mine, damn having bad internet in Australia)- Having to start from scratch even though you might have already spent hundreds of hours in DD1- Splitscreen/Local Co-Op has been removed. (I'm hoping for it to return though, as this is a huge con for me)- Survival Mode is forced ""Continuous"" which means (at the moment) No switching characters, and no chance to either stop, go pee/sammich/greet loved ones or, for the slow ones out there like me, loot/upgrade/repair without worrying of a DEW stabbing you in the♥♥♥♥♥♥- Textures start off super low res (But this is so you can get in the game faster) and download overtime as you play (As do maps), this can cause extra lag and make the game look very bad graphically, but just give it time and those sweet sweet graphics we've come to know and love will come rushing in! (It's a first time thing for everything, but after that first time everything will already be downloaded and therefore not a blurry low-res mess.All in all, I'm glad I bought it and will continue to play (hoping end-game RNG is fixed so we don't get max level gear with -50 stats)EDIT: I will be updating this as I experience new/more parts of the game!"
