76561197992014748,Recommended,302270,11373399,"Posted: 23 July, 2014",all,Lokbarith,"Hello, After seeing all of the reviews I wanted to write up my own little intake on the game thus far!To clarify. Micro transactions are to purchase EMOTES, not entire skins (thus far). When i launched the game i had all previous skins from the last game and some extras i had never purchased. alongside that all classes are able to be played with no additional purchase.There is 4 -5 new maps in the game currently, in addition to all the previous maps from the last game. On the website it states ""And more to come"" meaning there will be new maps made for this game in addition to what is avalible.The new UI is not terrible in my opinion, it takes time to adjust to and find out how it works, however once you figure out how it works it is fine. There is more armor slots in this game, with loot being purely for you. For example, the loot sysytem is similar to diablo where it only drops for you, only you can pick it up. this also applies to the chests before a map begins!To begin with the private server / SP option was disabled, but as the news update mentions, it has been re enabled and shall remain enabled. Trendy wanted to lower costs due to the fact the servers are hosted elsewhere to prevent hacking / cheating. However they realise this is a big mistake and have thusly rectified it.The gameplay is smooth, connection is also quite smooth. Here is a key bit of information - The game is mostly streamed, however I do not believe it streams the map EVERY TIME you want to play it. I believe it streams it the first time you load it and then you keep the file downloaded - This is most likely done to prevent an overload of downloads occuring and thus stressing the servers. It really isn't a hugely bad feature, it staggers people but not in a way that harms them playing the game or having access to it.All in all, yes DD2 may be close, however this is essential DD1, With all the old classes and skins, New maps, A better loot system, Visible armors (my personal favorite as i love to customise), New pets with abilities, Dyes to change the look of items,  New abilities that can be picked up and used in game (that scale off of two new stats, Hero Defensive Abillity and Heroes Offensive abillity)I would reccomend this game simply for the fact the new systems are interesting, it has been rebalanced to allow all classes to be viable for either DPS or for tower building, its not hugely expensive for what it is and micro transactions relaly has no influence on this game what so ever!"
