,Recommended,302270,11386431,"Posted: 23 July, 2014",all,Denther,"All the initial backlash to this game was blown way out of proportion.The online DRM is there but it actually works incredibly well. The UI seems kind of pasted on to the game but I've been matchmaking with 1-3 other friends and parties work fine and I've had no connection issues with about 5 hours of playing. The login is painless, doesn't require an email confirmation or really much of anything to get it to work. Steam remembers the information and you don't have to input it everytime you want to play. I saw a comparison of it to GFWL and almost laughed. It works great and even has Twitch integration (which I'll never use, but it's there).Singleplayer is present and works fine. This was not the case at launch but was fixed the day of release, mainly due to people being upset about its absence.As far as complaints of it being a ported mobile game I don't see this at all. I admittedly haven't played the original DD in about 2 years but the graphics fidelity is perfectly fine and doesn't seem any worse or better than before. I haven't done a side by side comparison, but it looks really good.My biggest complaint is the convultued inventory and character screens. Their messy and confusing and use icons for stats rather than just saying what it does. Locking and unlocking items is bizarre and crafting seems promising but I don't really understand it too well yet. Once a wiki comes out I'm sure it'll be easier to get it all down.As for the gameplay itself, it's a tweaked and polished DD. It's fun, it's intense, it's colorful, and it just works. I don't know what DLC is or isn't included, but I didn't own much in the original and there's definitely plenty of content for 6 bucks (what I paid) or the 15 or 20 it's going to be for new players. Definitely worth it.Get it."
