,Recommended,302270,11421816,"Posted: 26 July, 2014",all,Pandapop,"So far I am really enjoying this game, however, there are still some issues that need to be ironed out in my own opinion.Essentially it is a reboot of the same game, with a few additional maps, better scaling and quite interesting graphic and unlockable options, however, as it is early days there are some things that the developers need to address quite fast:1 - Time waiting for a private game. Mostly, I prefer to play my own games, especially at low level just to get a feel for my own playstyle and have a bit of fun without some rather nasty folks getting in my way. Yet even with a private game option, there is still a long countdown to the game start...no need to wait for other players if you're not expecting (or wanting) any.2 - The tavern needs some serious revamping. I can see where they were going with creating a community hub, but what they have really created is a lagfest extravaganza, not to mention, a headache. I would love to be able to comment on the purchaseable items and the changes in pet levelling, but I simply can't because I lose my mind after more than 4 minutes of looking in my itembox because Monk 56 wants to mess about with Aura's all over my bloody screen and the squire has created a dozen harpoon turrets that have rapid attack speed.3 - The timeout at the end of each level needs to be discontinued, or at least replaced with a 'Select another level' screen. Also, where on earth did the retry button go? You have to zone back in to the headache zone in order to try another level. And you don't get 'dwelling' time where you can inspect the drop items at the end of the game, you have a limited time to look at them and get out. Forcing you in the larger maps especially, to collect 10 tonnes of crap in your item box.4 - This is the big one. Why do I have to sit in an ever changing queue to play the game at all? So far I've spent a few hours playing the game, and more than double that waiting in a queue for a 'session' from the server. And the queueing system is pitiful, with me so far being 4th, 12th, 18th and 1st in the queue, but still not actually getting past the menu. More annoyingly, is that this doesn't seem to be a global issue. Only a few forum posts exist about it, and none of the guides or publicised material by Trendy make any reference to this. It is annoyingly bizarre.Overally, the bits that I have seen so far have been really grand, its just these very strange features that I can't seem to understand why they were created in the first place."
