,Recommended,302270,11435185,"Posted: 27 July, 2014",all,Ryzaria,"I like the game, I really do. New features and all that. It's like the reverse Borderlands effect. If you have no idea what that is, grab an umbrella, because I'm about to drop some knowledgeBorderlands was a good game, but its sequal only changed its map and the characters. The game mechanics essentially stayed the same.In Dungeon Defenders Eternity, the characters and maps from the first game are there (minus the DLC stuff, I might add) and the game mechanics really changed. Pets can use abilities, you can pick up amulets for more abilities, and the whole darn thing got balanced!Now, as you'd expect with some newer releases, it does have some bugs. The biggest one I think anyone who's played it is the matchmaking, which they even send notifications about if it's that bad. You'll sometimes be unable to find a game or even leave the Tavern.Overall, I really enjoy the game, and if they can fix that there matchmaking it'd be a really fantastic addition to the family of Dungeon Defenders."
